  "original_title": "38 \u0b95\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcb \u0bb9\u0bc6\u0bb0\u0bcb\u0baf\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bbe\u0baf\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0bae\u0b95\u0ba9\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Mother and son arrested with 38 kg of heroin",
      "author": "Digital Desk 5",
      "body_lines": [
        "Police Spokesperson Senior Superintendent of Police Nihal Taltuwa said that a mother and son were arrested with 38 kg of heroin in Ratnapura - Embilipitiya area.",
        "38kg 360g of heroin was seized by Mpilipitiya police on Monday (12). This amount of heroin was seized from a house near the Telecom office on Second Street in the city.",
        "A 46-year-old woman and a 22-year-old son of the said woman have been arrested from the house where the amount of heroin was seized.",
        "By claiming to be involved in the garment and bag manufacturing business, they have started the drug trade. Further investigations revealed that a brother of the arrested woman was also connected with this.",
        "They are involved in these activities under the guidance of the person who promotes drug smuggling from abroad.",
        "A digital scale used to measure heroin found on the arrested suspects was also seized.",
        "The police spokesperson further mentioned that further investigations are being carried out under the supervision of the Senior Superintendent of Police in charge of the Mpilipitiya Police Division to find out who the other suspects are."
      ],
